Student Management System (SMS) - Java
Overview
  *This project is a console-based Student Management System (SMS) built using Core Java. 
  *It allows users to perform CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations on student records. 
  *The system stores and retrieves student data from a file using serialization. 
  *It also includes features like searching, sorting, and filtering students by grade or name.

Features
  * Add Student: Add a new student with details like ID, Name, Age, Grade, and Email.
  * View All Students: Display all student records.
  * Search Student: Search for a student by their ID.
  * Update Student: Update student details (e.g., Name, Age, Grade, Email).
  * Delete Student: Delete a student record by ID.
  * File Storage: Store and retrieve student records from a file using serialization.
  * Search by Grade: Filter students by their grade. 
  * Sort Students: Sort students by name or grade.
  * Multithreading: Save data to a file in the background using a separate thread.

How to Run the Project
 * Prerequisites:
    * Install Java JDK 8 or higher.
    * Ensure java and javac are added to your system's PATH.

 * Steps:
     * Clone the repository or download the project files.
     * Navigate to the project directory in your terminal/command prompt.
     * Compile the Java files:
        -> javac -d . *.java
     * Run the application:
        -> java MiniProject.StudentManagerSystem

Project Structure
    StudentManagementSystem/
    ├── MiniProject/
    │   ├── Student.java              # Student class (POJO)
    │   ├── StudentManager.java       # Service layer for CRUD operations
    │   ├── StudentManagerSystem.java # Entry point of the application
    ├── students.txt                  # Serialized file for storing student records
    ├── README.md                     # Project documentation
